This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it deals with membership inference attacks on learned models. It may also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it discusses attacks on models and their potential implications for privacy. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks and their overfitting, which suggests it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments conducted on real-world datasets suggest that it could also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
